8

Access Token
These tokens usually have a short lifespan for security purpose. When it expires, the user must authenticate again to get a new access 
token limiting the exposure of the fact that it is a bearer token.
Access token must never be used for authentication.

Refresh Token
This token is a long-lived token compared to the access token and is used to request a new access token in cases where it is expired without user interaction.
It can be considered as credentials used to obtain access tokens.
It's allowed for long-lived access and highly confidential.
Refresh tokens can be used for grant types â€“ authorization code and password credentials grant.
Refresh tokens are intended for use only with authorization servers and are never sent to resource servers
